00:11:03.526 --> 00:11:04.836 A:middle
because they don't
have transparency.

00:11:05.696 --> 00:11:10.326 A:middle
We recommend having a logo
that's 256 pixels tall,

00:11:10.326 --> 00:11:13.066 A:middle
and then not more than
10 to 1 aspect ratio,

00:11:13.066 --> 00:11:14.796 A:middle
but don't make it any
wider than you need to.

00:11:15.226 --> 00:11:17.656 A:middle
Otherwise, it will make
it incredibly small

00:11:17.656 --> 00:11:19.116 A:middle
in some places like 4U Feeds.

00:11:19.116 --> 00:11:22.466 A:middle
If you can, avoid
things like copyrights

00:11:22.466 --> 00:11:24.916 A:middle
and trademarks alongside
your logo.

00:11:24.916 --> 00:11:27.416 A:middle
In many places, the logos
are very small on the screen,

00:11:27.756 --> 00:11:29.686 A:middle
and they just get lost
in the [inaudible].

00:11:30.626 --> 00:11:33.516 A:middle
And then, finally, with
promotional text or URL's,

00:11:33.516 --> 00:11:36.036 A:middle
you typically want to avoid
using those if you can.

00:11:36.186 --> 00:11:38.546 A:middle
The promotional text will be
very hard to read in places,

00:11:38.546 --> 00:11:39.936 A:middle
and just makes your
logo smaller.

00:11:39.936 --> 00:11:42.546 A:middle
And then URL's set
up the expectation

00:11:42.546 --> 00:11:45.846 A:middle
that they will be tappable,
