00:13:57.786 --> 00:14:00.236 A:middle
Let's briefly talk about RSS.

00:14:00.716 --> 00:14:03.116 A:middle
So when does it make
sense to use RSS?

00:14:04.076 --> 00:14:07.046 A:middle
So News supports displaying
articles from your RSS feed

00:14:07.046 --> 00:14:10.026 A:middle
if you have one, and it's
an appropriate solution

00:14:10.026 --> 00:14:13.386 A:middle
if you already have a website
or you already have an RSS feed,

00:14:13.516 --> 00:14:15.956 A:middle
and you want to get your content
into News really quickly.

00:14:16.776 --> 00:14:20.066 A:middle
But, ultimately, we only
really recommend using RSS

00:14:20.066 --> 00:14:23.056 A:middle
as a stepping stone to
get to Apple News format.

00:14:23.466 --> 00:14:26.576 A:middle
It's important to note that the
vast majority of articles read

00:14:26.576 --> 00:14:29.136 A:middle
in Apple News are using
Apple News format,

00:14:29.366 --> 00:14:30.806 A:middle
and so they're really engaging.

00:14:31.076 --> 00:14:33.996 A:middle
They have animations and
parallax and all of the things

00:14:33.996 --> 00:14:35.296 A:middle
that Apple News format allows.

00:14:35.656 --> 00:14:38.516 A:middle
And so if you're not using
Apple News format, it's a,

00:14:38.516 --> 00:14:41.066 A:middle
it's not a great comparison.

00:14:41.066 --> 00:14:43.596 A:middle
So we, it's always best
to use Apple News format.

00:14:43.596 --> 00:14:46.006 A:middle
But if you do need to use Apple
News format, or if you do need

00:14:46.006 --> 00:14:47.466 A:middle
to use RSS, these are some

00:14:47.626 --> 00:14:50.386 A:middle
of the features that,
that RSS supports.

00:14:50.386 --> 00:14:52.356 A:middle
Gives you the ability
to, to pull in images,

00:14:52.356 --> 00:14:53.526 A:middle
headlines, and excerpts.

00:14:54.166 --> 00:14:57.366 A:middle
We also show a preview
page of RSS articles

00:14:57.366 --> 00:14:58.606 A:middle
that it pulls from your feed.

00:14:59.016 --> 00:15:02.816 A:middle
And so this allows
those to, those previews

00:14:59.016 --> 00:15:02.816 A:middle
And so this allows
those to, those previews

00:15:02.816 --> 00:15:04.796 A:middle
to load really quickly
so we don't have

00:15:04.796 --> 00:15:06.146 A:middle
to load from your web page.

00:15:06.866 --> 00:15:08.506 A:middle
We host the RSS excerpt.

00:15:08.506 --> 00:15:11.566 A:middle
So when you use a [inaudible]
article, it loads immediately.

00:15:11.566 --> 00:15:13.596 A:middle
And then, of course,

00:15:13.596 --> 00:15:16.626 A:middle
you ultimately will host your
web page if users choose to tap

00:15:16.626 --> 00:15:18.526 A:middle
through to your web page.

00:15:19.986 --> 00:15:22.306 A:middle
So there's some best
practices for RSS.

00:15:22.306 --> 00:15:25.376 A:middle
You want to make your
preview full and enticing.

00:15:25.826 --> 00:15:29.186 A:middle
If you make it really short,
the odds are users will tap in,

00:15:29.186 --> 00:15:31.786 A:middle
see that it's only a sentence
or two, and then go back out

00:15:31.786 --> 00:15:34.066 A:middle
and look for one of the many
Apple News format articles

00:15:34.066 --> 00:15:36.046 A:middle
that offer a full experience.

00:15:37.696 --> 00:15:41.486 A:middle
So use long form, full
text RSS when you can,

00:15:42.186 --> 00:15:44.516 A:middle
and avoid links to
unrelated content.

00:15:44.816 --> 00:15:47.086 A:middle
Things like boilerplates,
article footers,

00:15:47.086 --> 00:15:49.836 A:middle
terms and conditions, user
agreements, privacy policies.

00:15:49.836 --> 00:15:52.226 A:middle
You don't really need
that in your preview,

00:15:52.366 --> 00:15:55.066 A:middle
and it just clutters up the
experience and takes away

00:15:55.066 --> 00:15:57.666 A:middle
from the simplicity and
the beauty of your article.

00:15:58.446 --> 00:16:01.526 A:middle
And then Apple News
already has built

00:15:58.446 --> 00:16:01.526 A:middle
And then Apple News
already has built

00:16:01.526 --> 00:16:05.066 A:middle
into some great sharing features
that users are accustomed

00:16:05.066 --> 00:16:07.366 A:middle
to using to share your
content is you don't need

00:16:07.366 --> 00:16:10.906 A:middle
to include links like tweet
this or like this on Facebook.

00:16:11.256 --> 00:16:13.126 A:middle
The app already takes
care of that, and, again,

00:16:13.126 --> 00:16:14.656 A:middle
it just adds noise
to your article.

00:16:15.496 --> 00:16:20.506 A:middle
Make sure your actual web page
is optimized for Safari on iOS.

00:16:20.656 --> 00:16:22.866 A:middle
The worst thing you can
have is a user follows

00:16:22.866 --> 00:16:24.386 A:middle
through the preview,
goes to your web page,

00:16:24.386 --> 00:16:26.926 A:middle
and then they have a big
desktop formatted website.

00:16:28.416 --> 00:16:30.246 A:middle
Then, finally, similar to
a point I made earlier,

00:16:30.406 --> 00:16:32.286 A:middle
make sure you provide a
dedicated point of contact.

